Subject: RE: [VB] transaxle conversion

  In the bus I'm building for cruising I cut the whole torsion out and am
welding in a late torsion, using and auto trans and a upright type 4 engine.
I will have to use a offset wheel to get it narrower or narrow the torsion
beam (apita) to get it to fit properly. 
  Creative engineering make a kit where you cut out the wishbones and weld
in there new ones to use the late trailing arms, pretty slick set up. 

ronnie

ps. If you go to Everetts site and look up Rich Barker and see his yellow
and blue panel it has late bus IRS suspension. The PO cut into the wishbones
and installed the pivots for using the late trailing arms (bus) without
having to narrow them. A very slick job, but he must of had 100 hours in the
fab work!

